## 5. Agent roster — who does what

| Agent | Purpose | Tools |
|---|---|---|
| **manager** (JARVIS) | Orchestration, task ledger, reviews, checkpoints, pitch decisions. | Read, Bash, Grep, Glob, WebFetch, WebSearch, Agent, colab-mcp, context7-mcp |
| **sde** | Product code: data pipelines, feature ETL, OpenDSS wrapper, dashboard, tests, CI. | All code + Playwright MCP |
| **ml-trainer** (NEW) | Compose + run Colab notebooks; train MTGNN, TFT, DCRNN; checkpoint to Drive; emit metrics reports. | Read/Write/Edit, Bash, colab-mcp, context7-mcp |
| **reviewer** | Pre-commit code review; flags bugs, security, scope creep. | Read, Grep, Glob, Bash, context7-mcp |
| **ui-verifier** | Drives Playwright against the Streamlit dashboard; clicks every control, screenshots, reports. | Playwright MCP |

**Parallelization contract:** at any time, ≤4 sub-agents run concurrently. Typical parallel fan-out: `sde(data pipeline)` + `sde(OpenDSS wrapper)` + `ml-trainer(smoke train)` + `sde(dashboard scaffold)`.

