## 9. Judge scorecard — what we optimise for

Inferred from "Scoring implication" paragraph in the brief:

| Dimension | Weight (est.) | Our hook |
|---|---|---|
| Arizona-orientation | High | IEEE 34/123 (34 is literally AZ); Phoenix NOAA; AZPS EIA-930; Maricopa ResStock; cite 8,631 MW peak + 2023 heat wave + $7M settlement. |
| Heat treatment depth | High | Heat-wave feature (≥3 consecutive days ≥110 °F); separate MAE on heat days; +10 °F and +15 °F stress scenarios. |
| EV treatment depth | High | EVI-Pro Lite fleet profiles; EV% slider; evening-peak alignment with APS EV Overnight TOU. |
| Decision-layer quality | Very High | Feeder-level risk score + top-3 drivers + ranked interventions + export CSV. |
| Model novelty / rigour | Medium | MTGNN + TFT ensemble; quantile reliability; physics-consistency via OpenDSS; transferability test (stretch). |
| Polished demo | Medium | Streamlit+pydeck map; 75-s reel; 5 slides. |

---

## 10. Definition of done

**Ready to submit when all are ✓:**
- [ ] `pytest -q` → 100% green on `tests/`.
- [ ] `streamlit run app/streamlit_app.py` → loads in <5s, all tabs render, no console errors.
- [ ] `reports/mtgnn_v1.md` exists with MAE, RMSE, MAPE (overall + heat-wave split), training time, GPU used.
- [ ] `reports/tft_v1.md` exists with quantile reliability plot (90% interval coverage ≥85%).
- [ ] OpenDSS physics check flags ≥1 voltage or thermal violation in +10°F scenario.
- [ ] README.md documents setup in ≤10 commands, model card included.
- [ ] `deck/slides.md` rendered to PDF (5 slides).
- [ ] `reel/final.mp4` is 60–90 s with voice-over or captions.
- [ ] GitHub repo tagged `v1.0-submission`, public, with LICENSE (MIT or Apache-2.0).
- [ ] Pitch text for submission form drafted in `submission.md`.

