## 11. Pitch deck — 5 slides (storyboard)

| # | Title | Content |
|---|---|---|
| 1 | **The grid problem Arizona is already failing at** | 54 days ≥110 °F in Phoenix 2024 · $7M heat-shutoff settlement · 500+ MW/hr duck-curve ramp. *Photo: Phoenix skyline + thermal overlay.* |
| 2 | **GridSense-AZ in one diagram** | Data-flow figure from §3.1; call out MTGNN + TFT + OpenDSS + decision layer. |
| 3 | **What it does that others don't** | Side-by-side: baseline vs +10°F scenario on feeder map; quantile reliability plot; top-3 drivers for feeder 17. |
| 4 | **Numbers** | MAE, RMSE, MAPE, heat-day MAE, quantile coverage, inference latency. One chart: error during heat wave vs normal. |
| 5 | **Why APS should care + what's next** | Screening for 2027 IRP capex; integration path with APS ADMS; next: real AMI fine-tune + DERMS orchestration. QR to GitHub. |

